pyspark.sql.functions.lpad

Left-pad the string column to width len with pad.

Parameters
col : Column or str
        target column to work on.

len : int
        length of the final string.

pad : str
        chars to prepend.

Returns : Column
        left padded result.

Examples

df = spark.createDataFrame([('abcd',)], ['s',])
df.select(lpad(df.s, 6, '#').alias('s')).collect()
[Row(s='##abcd')]
